Package demos.bags

Interface Bag<Item>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<Item>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DynamicallyShuffledBag, RandomAccessBag, StaticallyPerturbedBag
    public interface Bag<Item>
extends java.lang.Iterable<Item>
    A Bag<Item> is an Iterable<Item> which represents a rather useless data structure known as a bag. A bag allows for:
    • Initialization with a default or a provided capacity.
    • Querying for emptiness
    • Adding an element
    • "Shaking" the bag, which randomly perturbs the elements of the bag. This method will be crucial for our algorithmic analysis.
    Bags are allowed to grow arbitrarily. One cannot remove elements from a bag.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    jason
    See Also:
    Iterable
